  },
  "markup": "World wide, low level laser has the reputation for accelerating healing. \u0026nbsp;The use with wounds is starting to catch on here in the US. \u0026nbsp;\u0026nbsp;\u003Cbr style=\u0022border-radius: 0px ! important; color: #666666; font-family: citrixsans-regular,Helvetica Neue,Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: 20px; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;\u0022 /\u003E\nThere many studies published from a wide variety of healthcare fields demonstrating the positive effects of this safe and effective technology for wounds.\u0026nbsp;\u0026nbsp;\u003Cbr style=\u0022border-radius: 0px ! important; color: #666666; font-family: citrixsans-regular,Helvetica Neue,Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: 20px; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;\u0022 /\u003E\nJoin Dr. Chris Carraway and Dr. Janis Eells as they dive into the biology of \u0026nbsp;photobiomodulation and discuss the benefits of both local and systemic protocols and their individual benefits in this area."
}]]></Value>
    </description>
